         <div class="key-point">
          <h3>What is an Agreement in Principle?</h3>
          <p>
            An agreement in principle is a document issued by a mortgage broker or a lender which indicates that you are likely to be accepted for a loan up to a certain value. 
          </p>
          <p>
            It is common for a buyer to seek out an agreement in principle as early in the mortgage application stage as possible in order to manage expectations and allow the buyer to fully understand how much they could potentially borrow, how much of a deposit they would need and roughly how much the monthly payments would be.
          </p>
          <p>
            Lenders do not underwrite documents when a mortgage agreement in principle is processed therefore it is not  a guarantee to lend, once you submit a full application you will have to send off payslips, Bank Statements etc which will be fully assessed before any offer can be made.
          </p>
          <p>
            It is common practice for an estate agent to request an agreement in principle before accepting a bid on a property, therefore is is in your best interests to have one in place before you even begin to look at properties.

            <a href="/agreement-in-principle-booking">Get your agreement in principle now!</a>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid alt-color">
