          <h3>What information will I need to supply for an agreement in principle?</h3>
          <p>
            When applying for an agreement in principle you will have to supply personal information that will include your name date of birth etc, details regarding your address history, employment history, your committed expenditure and details regarding any adverse credit.
          </p>
          <p>
            The amount of information required will depend on which lender you apply to as they all ask their own unique question sets.
          </p>
          <p>
            Many online mortgage broker firms offer their own branded agreement in principles, many of these are unreliable and are more like affordability calculations rather than actual agreement in principles. An affordability calculation is no use to anyone if your credit score does not support the application. 
          </p>
          <p>
            Mortgages Northern Ireland make sure that the agreement in principle you get from us has been credit scored and is an accurate reflection of what a lender is likely to offer you.
          </p>
         </div>
